author: THISWEEK NEWSPAPERS
title: school tennis | Area teams advance to state doubles semifinals
text:
MASON, Ohio — The percentages are in favor of central Ohio adding to its string of four consecutive Division I doubles championships, and there’s an even chance of that title coming from one of Ohio’s tradition-rich girls tennis programs.
During Friday’s opening day of the state tournament, three of the four surviving teams from the first two rounds came from the area.
The Upper Arlington teams of Kyra Jung and Anna Marie Reynolds and Olivia Kompa and Paige Kompa will play against each other in one semifinal.
In addition, the Olentangy Liberty doubles team of Anna Delaney and Lexi Steer will face the Cincinnati Ursuline Academy duo of Jenny Duma and Gabriella O’Connor in a semifinal.
“It’s so exciting,” Paige Kompa said. “I’m with my sister. She’s a senior, and now I get to do it with her.”
The Kompas, who beat Jung and Reynolds in a district semifinal and Delaney and Steer for the district title, opened their state tournament with a 6-1, 6-0 win over Avon’s Maddie Nakon and Ana Lopez. They then beat Mason’s Isabel Cepeda and Sneha Kadi 6-0, 6-2 in a quarterfinal.
Jung and Reynolds opened by beating North Canton Hoover’s Lynn Daugherty and Sydney Bergman 6-2, 6-3, but they had more trouble in their quarterfinal, rallying to win 2-6, 6-2, 6-0 to set up the matchup among teammates.
“I think it’s kind of weird,” Jung said of preparing to play the Kompas. “Hopefully we can beat them this time.”
The Liberty doubles team opened by beating Cuyahoga Falls Walsh Jesuit’s Skye Harwood and Megan Hissong 6-1, 6-1, then edged Canfield’s Hannah Cianciola and Ashley Kaleel 6-4, 7-5 in a quarterfinal.
“It’s amazing, since I’ve never even qualified for state before,” said Delaney, a senior. “I’m just so happy. We both just started hitting more balls in.”
